We all have our fears right? Things that scare us or cause us to be anxious. What might cause anxiety in one person might not be the same for another. - Well, believe it or not, being away from home has always given me a lot of anxiety. My introverted(extrovert) heart looooves to stay home in my comfort zone where it is safe and everything is good. Home is what calms me. (I’m sure you never could guess that by looking at my highlight reel of pics) BUT... it hasn’t always been this way. I used to NEVER leave home because of how much anxiety it caused. Until I finally got so sick of that anxiety dictating my life! I forced myself to be in the uncomfortableness in order to actually feel alive and enjoy life!! Its always a work in progress:). So if you are wondering why I chose to travel across the whole US solo, this is why ❤️ It scares the crap out of me. And I never thought I could do it. Life wins this time, not the fear!
Peace is her priority ✨
